       <p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>
       <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row">
            
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="card card-plain">
                    <div class="header">
                        <h4 class="title">About Us</h4>
                        <p class="category">Who are we?</p>
                        <br>
                        <%= image_tag("vadim.jpg", :alt => "developer", :class => "portrait") %> 
                        <br>  <br>
                        <p>Greetings, my name is Vadim Malakhovski and I am the single developer of this fantasic web application, so when I said "we" I meant "I".</p> 
                        <br>
                        <p>I am a computer science student at NCI Ireland and this is my final project.</p> 
                        <br>
                        <p> So what is a SchoolApp?</p>
                        <p> In a nutshell SchoolApp is an electronic school journal which enables records of studentsâ€™ academic and behavioural performance. </p> 
                        <p>SchoolApp also has inbuilt statistical analysis and comment analysis functions to provide teachers, parents and  students with this vital data.</p>
                        <br>
                        <p>Let me share some of the main functionalities offered by this application:</p>
                        <p>1. Creating an account.</p> 
                        <p>2. Viewing a student and all the academic and behavioural results + comments associated with that student.</p> 
                        <p>3. Creating and storing a filter which would always display a student through that filter.</p> 
                        <p>4. Teacher have additional functionalities. They can search, create, mark and edit students.</p> 
                        <p>5. All the users can also read school articles and watch this youtube tutorial. 
                        </p> 
                    </div>
                    

                    
                    

                    
                    
